Algorithm
Initialize the graph and heuristic values.
Create an empty priority queue (OPEN list).
Insert the source node into the priority queue with its heuristic value.
Mark the source as visited.
Repeat until the priority queue becomes empty:
Remove the node having the smallest heuristic value.
If the selected node is the goal node, terminate the search.
Otherwise, expand all its neighboring nodes.
For every unvisited neighbor:
Mark it as visited.
Store its parent.
Insert it into the priority queue based on its heuristic value.
Trace back from the goal node to the source using the parent dictionary.
Display the path found.
